  "title": "Test Engineer (Advantest V93k/Teradyne Uflex)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Develop and debug test programs for Digital, PMIC, RF &amp; Mixed Signal products on <strong>ATE platforms (Advantest 93k – SmarTest 7/8, Teradyne UFLEX)</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with design engineers on first silicon bring-up, device characterization across PVT, and production release.</li>\n  <li>Perform digital vector debug (JTAG, SCAN, ATPG, Functional, MBIST) and characterize Mixed Signal IPs (ADC, DAC, PLL, etc.).</li>\n  <li>Support production ramp-up, yield improvement, and test time optimization through cross-functional teamwork.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Electronics/Electrical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of Test Engineering experience, with hands-on skills in <strong>Teradyne UltraFlex</strong> or <strong>Advantest 93K ATE</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of analog and digital electronics.</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a passion for hands-on work in a lab environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br>\nRegistration: R21100996</p>",
